<h2 style="text-align: center">SOIL TESTING</h2>

<p>Soil Test is the analysis of a soil sample to determine nutrient and contaminant content, composition and other characteristics such as acidity or pH level.
<p style="text-align: right">(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soil_test)

\image image1
<br>Fig. 1. Soil Testing

<p><b>Objectives of soil testing: -</b> 
<p style="margin-left: 150px;">1. To estimate the available nutrient status, reaction (acidic/alkaline) of a soil.
<br>2. To evaluate the fertility status of soils of a country or a state or a district, and change in its pattern due to crop cultivation over a period of years.
<br>3. Checking sufficiency and deficiency of nutrients (e.g. - N, P, K)
<br>4. To prepare a basis for fertilizer recommendation.
<p style="text-align: right">(http://megapib.nic.in/soil%20testing.htm)

<p><b>Indicators for soil type and quality: -</b> 
<p>
<table border=1 style="border-collapse:collapse;margin-left: 100px;margin-right: 100px;">
	</tbody>
		<tr>
			<th>Indicator category
