	</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center">Table 3.4. Indicators of soil type and quality
<p style="text-align: right">(http://soilquality.org/indicators.html)

<p><b>Ideal indicators should:</b>
<p style="margin-left: 150px;"> &#8226 correlate well with ecosystem processes
<br> &#8226 integrate soil physical, chemical, and biological properties & processes
<br> &#8226 be accessible to many users
<br> &#8226 be sensitive to management & climate
<br> &#8226 be components of existing databases
<br> &#8226 be interpretable
<p style="text-align: right">(http://soilquality.org/indicators.html)

<p><b>Laboratory work: -</b>
<p style="margin-left: 150px;">1. testing pH
<br>2. testing nutrients
<br>3. testing electrical conductivity
<br>4. testing soil enzymes
<br>5. testing organic compounds
